## Session Start

When starting a session, read `.planning/STATE.md` for current position,
recent decisions, and open items. This orients you without requiring a
full context re-read of the codebase.

If context compacts mid-session: preserve current task context in STATE.md
before compaction completes. After compaction, re-read `.planning/STATE.md`
to restore orientation. Hooks handle this automatically ‚Äî focus on keeping
STATE.md accurate.

## Two Systems

This project uses two complementary systems for continuity:

**instruction system** (static, human-curated) ‚Äî defines HOW to work:
- `CLAUDE.md` ‚Äî project identity and behavioral guidance
- `.claude/rules/` ‚Äî conventions, session protocol, guardrails
- `.claude/settings.json` ‚Äî tool permissions and hook configurations
- `.claude/hooks/` ‚Äî automated session-start and session-end behavior

**learning system** (dynamic, session-updated) ‚Äî captures WHAT is happening:
- `.planning/STATE.md` ‚Äî current position, decisions, open items (shared via git)
- Auto memory ‚Äî user preferences and cross-session insights (machine-local)

Instructions stay stable across sessions. State evolves with each session.

