## Auto Memory

Keep auto memory under 200 lines. Use an index + topic pattern to stay organized:
save a short index entry per topic and expand only when needed. Prefer
`.planning/STATE.md` for critical project state ‚Äî STATE.md is shared via git,
auto memory is machine-local and not visible to collaborators.

**Provenance:** When saving a memory entry, include context so future sessions
can judge whether it's still accurate:
- **source:** where this came from (user-stated, observed-in-code, inferred, external-doc)
- **trust:** high (user explicitly said it) | medium (observed pattern) | low (model inference)
- **validated:** date last confirmed accurate

Example: `[source:user-stated, trust:high, validated:{{DATE}}] Project uses PostgreSQL`

Note: `autoMemoryDirectory` and `autoMode` must be set in user or local settings,
not project settings (`.claude/settings.json`). Project settings are shared via git
and cannot safely carry machine-specific paths.

